{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d66e57e2-e8ba-4e0c-862b-87a8719a175c","content":"You can filter by class name using the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nOr more precisely by class:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nIf the class is in a namespace (e.g., `MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests`), you can also use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so it matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e6d27744-1f70-4a73-86c0-76c9509fc64d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. Let me look at the test file to understand the structure.","outputTokens":207,"requestId":"CFDF:B84BF:14224B0:177A428:69EC1550"},"id":"e7f93026-6664-435d-bb88-a3eb4a11f0ca","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:13:57.485Z","parentId":"0616b616-16ce-44fb-9f1f-deb3f246c253"}
